{"sha": "e7b8e6fbca483edbf723105c5b7ede94f1caebe8", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmU3YjhlNmZiY2E0ODNlZGJmNzIzMTA1YzViN2VkZTk0ZjFjYWViZTg=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "bors[bot]", "email": "26634292+bors[bot]@users.noreply.github.com", "date": "2021-05-14T17:15:21Z"}, "committer": {"name": "GitHub", "email": "noreply@github.com", "date": "2021-05-14T17:15:21Z"}, "message": "Merge #8819\n\n8819: Use package root as `cargo check` working directory r=matklad a=bcully\n\nCargo commands are affected by the `.cargo/config` files above\r\ntheir working directory. If cargo is invoked from above the directory\r\nholding `Cargo.toml`, it may not pick up important settings like\r\nregistry replacements, causing it to behave differently or even fail.\r\n\r\nMost cargo invocations are currently setting their working directories\r\nto the directory containing `Cargo.toml`, but a couple of paths remain\r\nin which cargo is invoked from the default workspace root instead.\r\n\r\nThis change fixes that, resolving some cargo check failures that I\r\nexperienced in a multi-root workspace in which packages used different\r\nregistries.\n\nCo-authored-by: Brendan Cully <brendan@cully.org>", "tree": {"sha": "e5466afadb494c691ebb9b28208b57409ecc4de6", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/e5466afadb494c691ebb9b28208b57409ecc4de6"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/e7b8e6fbca483edbf723105c5b7ede94f1caebe8", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": true, "reason": "valid", "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\nwsBcBAABCAAQBQJgnrApCRBK7hj4Ov3rIwAA0VYIAH4SwaVgSY8sJ5BfdJf12FN4\nrYrkLtK8VdSTjBc0hb/O2RNBl8LOQT7G+J0AsURB2bcyeRP3ENN3jeyh/QaWJH8b\nF59bFPRklR7D4IDulUrRd1ZUEW1SNossRqzkFTvzWPLhI6+plJlOt7BCBvM4rDrp\nyUPxHQT4K82IqLsKMPZNxKm5VqbyDNDvpHvhH2SPTWNHfFqCh8k+9mW1B4rcD8tQ\nu8IZTEPpr1PqkYAicsjmQvHyq0YhBfLRl06XnD12ELRglcxluwE9F30SgYhv9qv6\nL9NS+ABPGwZcCfRqsVYQcJ+aEXz+mpkH16DIPheyeZT6K5c6fR1Ttr4LsjGLwXI=\n=/4On\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----\n", "payload": "tree e5466afadb494c691ebb9b28208b57409ecc4de6\nparent 6c0f20d79f8e5da57bd907aa1c3324fb92344b9a\nparent c4664609ed0f8b430285de99b4f7a8cc0ae655f5\nauthor bors[bot] <26634292+bors[bot]@users.noreply.github.com> 1621012521 +0000\ncommitter GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1621012521 +0000\n\nMerge #8819\n\n8819: Use package root as `cargo check` working directory r=matklad a=bcully\n\nCargo commands are affected by the `.cargo/config` files above\r\ntheir working directory. If cargo is invoked from above the directory\r\nholding `Cargo.toml`, it may not pick up important settings like\r\nregistry replacements, causing it to behave differently or even fail.\r\n\r\nMost cargo invocations are currently setting their working directories\r\nto the directory containing `Cargo.toml`, but a couple of paths remain\r\nin which cargo is invoked from the default workspace root instead.\r\n\r\nThis change fixes that, resolving some cargo check failures that I\r\nexperienced in a multi-root workspace in which packages used different\r\nregistries.\n\nCo-authored-by: Brendan Cully <brendan@cully.org>\n"}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/e7b8e6fbca483edbf723105c5b7ede94f1caebe8", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/e7b8e6fbca483edbf723105c5b7ede94f1caebe8", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/e7b8e6fbca483edbf723105c5b7ede94f1caebe8/comments", "author": {"login": "bors[bot]", "id": 26634292, "node_id": "MDM6Qm90MjY2MzQyOTI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/1847?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors%5Bbot%5D", "html_url": "https://github.com/apps/bors", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors%5Bbot%5D/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/use